01:37:00.130 --> 01:37:02.000
that they might someday
become full-time employees.

01:37:02.000 --> 01:37:07.870
I was assigned to my first
choice, editorial, and was placed

01:37:07.870 --> 01:37:12.130
in Cartwheel Books, a Scholastic
imprint for very young readers.

01:37:12.130 --> 01:37:15.960
That summer I read a lot
of slush, unsolicited

01:37:15.960 --> 01:37:18.060
and unagented [phonetic]
manuscripts,

01:37:18.060 --> 01:37:23.440 position:56%
wrote a lot of reader's reports, and
wrote a lot of rejection letters.

01:37:23.440 --> 01:37:26.100
But I also got the opportunity
to write the first draft

01:37:26.100 --> 01:37:31.060
of an early reader, and everyone
I worked with was really nice.

01:37:31.060 --> 01:37:34.320
In addition to our departmental
duties, the fellows had to work

01:37:34.320 --> 01:37:35.620
on a group project together.

01:37:35.620 --> 01:37:40.840
We were tasked with developing a
book proposal with Doug E. Fresh

01:37:40.840 --> 01:37:43.770
that would be presented at
an acquisitions meeting.

01:37:43.770 --> 01:37:47.710
It was very cool and I was like,
yes, this is what editors do.

01:37:47.710 --> 01:37:51.250
They develop book proposals
with a human beatbox [laughter].

01:37:52.370 --> 01:37:54.930
But it wasn't all fun, games,
and sitting around coming

01:37:54.930 --> 01:37:57.800
up with clever ideas
with Doug E. Fresh.

01:37:57.800 --> 01:38:00.410
In addition to our departmental
duties and the work we did

01:38:00.410 --> 01:38:03.290
on the group project
evenings and weekends,

01:38:03.290 --> 01:38:05.120
