01:38:07.060 --> 01:38:10.660
During these meeting we would
discuss the articles and books

01:38:10.660 --> 01:38:13.400
that Karen had assigned
to us as required reading,

01:38:13.400 --> 01:38:17.980
pieces about leadership, diversity,
corporate culture, and success.

01:38:17.980 --> 01:38:23.120
And we would also talk about
all our little intern drama,

01:38:23.120 --> 01:38:26.120
because that housing I
mentioned that was provided, we,

01:38:26.120 --> 01:38:29.250
the fellows who worked together
so intensely on the group project,

01:38:29.250 --> 01:38:32.730
and we're already around
each other for so many hours,

01:38:32.730 --> 01:38:34.030
we also lived together

01:38:34.030 --> 01:38:36.980
in [inaudible] College
Housing in Manhattan.

01:38:36.980 --> 01:38:41.560
This was a very intense, very
different sort of bonding.

01:38:41.560 --> 01:38:46.790
I was always tired and I struggled
to find time and space to be alone.

01:38:46.790 --> 01:38:49.660
But I was working harder than
I ever had up until that point.

01:38:49.660 --> 01:38:51.350
I was learning.

01:38:51.350 --> 01:38:52.650
I was growing.

01:38:52.650 --> 01:38:56.500
And I was, somewhat
reluctantly, stretching.

01:38:56.500 --> 01:39:00.030
The five of us were being urged
to reach deep inside ourselves

01:39:00.030 --> 01:39:04.930
and bring forth every fiber of
our potential, and it was hard.

01:39:04.930 --> 01:39:07.770
And while both living and
working with the same small group

01:39:07.770 --> 01:39:11.840 position:56%
of people could be painful at times,
who knows if those of us who weren't

01:39:11.840 --> 01:39:15.550 position:56%
from New York could have figured out
how to be a summer intern in big,

01:39:15.550 --> 01:39:19.030
confusing, expensive New York City.

01:39:19.030 --> 01:39:21.870
Sponsored housing was
essential to my --

01:39:21.870 --> 01:39:25.650 position:56%
was essential to my participation in
the program and part of why I'm able

01:39:25.650 --> 01:39:29.020
to be here today at the
Library of Congress [laughter].

01:39:29.020 --> 01:39:31.860
And here's a fun fact,
