01:40:25.970 --> 01:40:29.720
of diverse writers and artists that
the entire company was invited to.

01:40:29.720 --> 01:40:34.950
And the third summer our group
project gave us the opportunity

01:40:34.950 --> 01:40:37.020
to travel to New Orleans.

01:40:37.020 --> 01:40:41.090
It was one year after Hurricane
Katrina, and we were tasked meeting

01:40:41.090 --> 01:40:44.120
with educators and
librarians and then presenting

01:40:44.120 --> 01:40:46.890
to Scholastic what we
learned along with a plan

01:40:46.890 --> 01:40:51.230 position:56%
for how Scholastic could help the
schools and libraries still in need.

01:40:51.230 --> 01:40:57.860
At this point I had graduated and
had three transformative summers

01:40:57.860 --> 01:40:59.750
as a Scholastic CDF Fellow.

01:40:59.750 --> 01:41:04.980
By that time I had decided
I want to be an editor.

01:41:04.980 --> 01:41:06.760
When I thought about it
it made perfect sense.

01:41:06.760 --> 01:41:10.760
And at Scholastic I could use my
English degree as well as invoke

01:41:10.760 --> 01:41:14.360
that abandoned early
childhood development major.

01:41:14.360 --> 01:41:18.470
All I needed was to be exposed
to editorial as a career path

01:41:18.470 --> 01:41:21.790
and a realistic chance
at making it happen.

01:41:21.790 --> 01:41:25.750
My third summer as a fellow
