03:05:16.010 --> 03:05:18.340
I mean, I think you have to decide
for yourself what are those lines,

03:05:18.340 --> 03:05:19.860
and that comes from
how are you raised?

03:05:19.860 --> 03:05:23.900
You know, what are
your ideas and ideals?

03:05:23.900 --> 03:05:29.460
What kind of artistic and writerly
integrity are you going to have?

03:05:29.460 --> 03:05:30.760
And you got to decide that.

03:05:30.760 --> 03:05:34.020
And the thing is, if
you just yourself,

03:05:34.020 --> 03:05:36.930
if you're just authentic you
can never sort of get caught,

03:05:36.930 --> 03:05:41.380
or get caught up because
you're always being yourself.

03:05:41.380 --> 03:05:45.280
Nikki likes to say, or in this -- I
quote this a lot in this interview

03:05:45.280 --> 03:05:47.690
with Claudia Tait [assumed
spelling] of black women writers,

03:05:47.690 --> 03:05:51.240
Nikki talked about
dancing naked on the floor.

03:05:51.240 --> 03:05:56.790
And you do it and, if you like
it, cool, if you don't, go home,

03:05:56.790 --> 03:05:58.290
but I'm going to do what I do.

03:05:58.290 --> 03:06:01.590
I think you just got to
do that, whatever it is.

03:06:01.590 --> 03:06:05.440
And it may evolve because
we don't remain the same.

03:06:05.440 --> 03:06:10.160
We grow, but you do have to be
authentic, that's what I think.

03:06:10.160 --> 03:06:13.770
